main event: Five people in a boat observed multiple unidentified objects in the sky on August 26, 1959.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for approximately 11 minutes,The objects appeared as faint lights, moving at about 40 mph, observers saw up to 6 objects visible at different times during the sighting, One object moved from one end of the Big Dipper to the other in about 3 seconds, The lights were described as yellowish white, similar in size to first magnitude stars.
sighted object: multiple unidentified lights in the sky
witness description: five individuals in a boat traveling from Winneconne to Oshkosh
